gmtoolkit — third-party acknowledgements
=========================================

gmtoolkit is a re-implementation of the subset of the GameMaker Studio
data.win pipeline that many ARM64-handheld ports need at install
time. Some of its source trees are direct C++ ports of upstream code,
and those files carry the upstream's license (GPL-3 or MPL-2). See
LICENSE.md for the per-tree breakdown; this NOTICE is just attribution.

Every ported source file records the upstream file it was derived from
and the upstream commit it was pinned to, in a header comment of the
form:

    // Port of <upstream/path/X.cs>
    // Source: github.com/UnderminersTeam/<repo> @ <short-sha>
    // SPDX-License-Identifier: <license>


UndertaleModTool / UndertaleModLib
  https://github.com/UnderminersTeam/UndertaleModTool
  License: GPL-3.0-or-later
  Pinned commit: c4e5c2c3

  Used as the authoritative reference for the GameMaker data.win
  format: FORM/IFF chunk layout, per-chunk versioning quirks, the
  SOND/AUDO/AGRP/VARI/FUNC/STRG/TXTR/CODE/SHDR/SCPT/GLOB structures,
  and the version-detection heuristics that bump GMS revision based on
  on-disk format deltas.

  C++ ports of UTMT live under (all GPL-3-or-later in our tree):
    * include/GMSLib/**, src/GMSLib/** -- UndertaleModLib/ (Models +
      Compiler bridge, plus UndertaleChunks.cs CheckForGM*() in
      SaveBackend/VersionDetect.cpp)


Underanalyzer
  https://github.com/UnderminersTeam/Underanalyzer
  License: MPL-2.0
  Pinned commit: 4be8217

  Used as the reference for the GML compiler pipeline: lexer, parser,
  AST nodes, bytecode generation, instruction patching, version-flag
  gating, the entire CompileContext orchestration.

  C++ ports of Underanalyzer live under (all MPL-2 in our tree):
    * include/Underanalyzer/**, src/Underanalyzer/**


GameMaker Audio Tools (gmKtool / GMblob.py)
  https://github.com/Kotzebuedog/gmtools
  License: GPL-3.0-or-later

  Used as the reference for SOND-driven audio compression and the
  SOND-flag / AUDO-format invariant maintained during WAV->OGG
  conversion (GMblob.GMdata.audio_enable_compress). Our implementation
  in src/Toolkit/CompressAudio.cpp is independent C++ on top of
  libvorbis, not a port of the Python; the algorithm-level behaviour
  (which entries to compress, when to flip the IsCompressed bit, how
  to slide SOND in lockstep with AUDO) is sourced from there.


